<DOCNO>FT922-11861</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CDWA1ACWFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>920423
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  23 APR 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There are no wool sales to test auction demand and price changes before the
Easter recess gave no entirely definate lead on market direction. Most
international observers seem to think that competition for available
supplies will be sufficient to feep prices rising for the remainder of the
season, until the end of June. Demand from China has been good this season
and is believed likely to remain so for the rest of the season, helping to
offset severe problems in the old Soviet Union and Eastern European areas.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 34
