of 1989 - had made an important contribution to the improved lending margin.
These accounts originally cost most Spanish banks dear after they joined
battle with Santander but the high interest rates originally being offered
have since cooled considerably.
Despite Santander's good first quarter figures, banking analysts in Madrid
are still predicting a difficult year for local banks.
