</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Jessups, the Essex-based motor dealer, returned to profit with Pounds
189,000 pre-tax for the six months to February 29, compared with a Pounds
189,000 loss last time.
Mr John Ganney, finance director, said the swing into the black had been
achieved through cost-cutting and a reduction in interest charges.
