FT  23 APR 92 / UK Company News: Ross at Pounds 1.3m in first results since
full listing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ROSS GROUP, the rapidly growing packaging and electronics company, yesterday
unveiled profits of Pounds 1.26m in its first full set of annual results
since coming to the main market through last year's reverse takeover of
Whittington Group, the giftware company.
Mr Noel Hayes, group managing director, said the results were not comparable
with the Pounds 647,000 loss reported in 1990, as that year's figures
represented only Whittington's performance.
All of Whittington's businesses had been sold since the takeover, resulting
in a below-the-line gain of Pounds 3.5m, he said.
Comparing the businesses before Whittington with the current Ross Group,
pre-tax profits for the year to December 31 rose from Pounds 989,000. This
year's result had been depressed by offsetting the Pounds 400,000 costs of
closing Whittington's head office against the operating profits.
Mr Hayes said the group had increased its market share in both the packaging
and consumer electronics divisions. The introduction of new products, such
as camcorder batteries, had boosted consumer electronics, while 'hard work'
and new contracts had helped packaging.
The acquisition of Traveller International in April had contributed about
Pounds 150,000 to profits, Mr Hayes said.
Stellar, the seventh company acquired by Ross in the last 18 months, had
made a marginal contribution to profits as it was included for just one
month.
Stellar's loss-making Brighouse site - which produces battery chargers and
electrical plugs and accounted for about Pounds 2m in losses last year -
made a marginal deficit in the first quarter, Mr Hayes said.
Net debt stood at Pounds 4.5m, representing about 28 per cent of
shareholders' funds.
The final dividend is 0.3p, making a total of 0.45p. Earnings per share were
1.5p.
</TEXT>
