UNISYS, the long-struggling US computer manufacturer, yesterday reported
much better-than-expected first-quarter earnings, boosting hopes for a
successful turnround after years of heavy losses.
Many analysts had projected a loss for the quarter but the company unveiled
net income of Dollars 48.3m, or 11 cents a share. In the same period last
year Unisys recorded net losses of Dollars 98.2m, or 79 cents.
The result was the second consecutive quarterly gain for the company, which
