93m in Blockbuster common stock. Philips, a Dutch company, also holds an
option to acquire 5m additional shares of Blockbuster stock before December
15.
If Philips exercises the entire option, it would hold about 7.1 per cent of
the video company's outstanding shares, Blockbuster said.
At the end of the quarter, there were 2,829 Blockbuster video stores, of
which 1,805 were company owned and 1,024 franchised.
