<TEXT>
AMERICAN Brands, the US tobacco and drinks group, said fluctuations in
exchange rates for foreign currencies, principally sterling, had adversely
affected income by Dollars 11m, or 5 cents a share, in the latest quarter,
AP-DJ reports.
However, the group lifted first-quarter net income to Dollars 245.2m, from
