FT  22 APR 92 / Chamber sees signs of recovery
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE DECLINE in manufacturing output is slowing and there are signs of
recovery, according to a survey published yesterday by the London Chamber of
Commerce and Industry.
A total of 38 per cent of manufacturers said orders for the first quarter
were up for the first time in two years, although 30 per cent reported a
fall in orders. The balance of 8 per cent is the first positive figure for
two years. A balance of 7 per cent of service-sector companies reported a
fall in orders, while in the previous quarter a balance of 1 per cent
expected a rise.
