FT  22 APR 92 / Ucatt announces redundancies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UCATT, the construction union, is to make redundant nearly 10 per cent of
its staff because of a decline in membership.
Last year the union had a Pounds 500,000 deficit and lost at least 5,000
members. Membership stands at just over 200,000.
Sixteen clerical workers will lose their jobs, out of a total of 181
officials and staff.
Criteria by which the redundancies will be selected have yet to be agreed
with the GMB general union which represents the clerical workers.
Mr George Brumwell, Ucatt general secretary, said the cuts were aimed at
enabling the union to 'weather the recession and stay independent'.
