<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 92 / Rome to host peace negotiations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROGER MATTHEWS, Middle East Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MIDDLE EAST peace negotiations will move to Rome after the next round of
talks, which are scheduled to open in Washington on Monday, the US State
Department announced yesterday.
The new venue represents a modest step forward in resolving the procedural
difficulties which have delayed consideration of substantive issues.
Syria, Jordan, Lebanon and the Palestinian delegation had strongly resisted
Israel's efforts to site the talks closer to the Middle East. They felt it
was to their advantage to hold the early bilateral sessions in the US where
pressure from the administration and the attention of the media worked to
their advantage.
In order to break the deadlock, the State Department asked each delegation
to submit a list of acceptable venues. Rome was common to the five lists. No
date has been set for the first meeting in Italy and may have to await the
outcome of the general election in Israel on June 23.
</TEXT>
