FT  22 APR 92 / Output decline seen to slow
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE DECLINE in manufacturing output is slowing and there are signs the
recession is beginning to lift, according to a survey published yesterday by
the London Chamber of Commerce and Industry.
A total of 38 per cent of manufacturers said orders for the first quarter
this year were up for the first time in two years, although 30 per cent
reported a fall. The balance of 8 per cent is the first positive figure for
two years.
A balance of 7 per cent of companies in the service sector reported a fall
in orders compared with a balance of 1 per cent expecting a rise in the
previous quarter.
