FT  22 APR 92 / World Trade News: Fiat offshoot in Russian 'Arctic' deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
IVECO, the commercial vehicles subsidiary of Italy's Fiat group, has reached
a co-operation agreement with Russia's Uralaz trucks producer to make
heavy-duty vehicles for use in Arctic conditions, Haig Simonian reports from
Milan.
No details about the value or production volumes of the deal have been
revealed. But it is believed to be the first agreement of its kind between a
Russian and western company in the heavy-vehicles sector, and could lead to
close co-operation between the two groups.
Iveco will supply Uralaz, based in the Urals city of Miass, with technology
to assemble a new range of trucks designed to operate in temperatures down
to -55 degrees Celsius. The new models will complement the existing vehicles
made by Uralaz. which currently makes about 30,000 trucks a year. The accord
also calls for extending the collaboration in production of non-Arctic
models.
