<HEADLINE>
FT  21 APR 92 / International Company News: Abitibi-Price deeper in red
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ABITIBI-Price, the Canadian forest products company 82 per cent-owned by
property developer Olympia &amp; York, has entered its third consecutive year in
the red.
The unremitting weakness in the newsprint market pushed Abitibi to a
first-quarter loss of CDollars 41.6m, (USDollars 35.2m) or 61 cents a share,
from a CDollars 5.5m loss, or 9 cents a share, a year earlier. Losses
totalled CDollars 75.9m last year and CDollars 44.6m in 1990. First-quarter
revenues dipped by 10 per cent to CDollars 650m.
As one of O&amp;Y's non-property assets, Abitibi is a candidate for disposal to
ease the parent company's liquidity crunch. However, O&amp;Y would prefer not to
sell the company at the bottom of the forest products cycle.
</TEXT>
